Emergency services responded to a fire at Newbridge Silverware on Friday evening. The building contains facilities including a shop, cafe and exhibition space. It is understood the blaze was relatively minor and was not being treated as suspicious. It was brought under control by firefighters just after 10pm. In a statement gardaí said they attended the scene of a fire at a business premises in Newbridge, County Kildare. “Local Fire Services also attended the scene in order to extinguish the fire. No injuries were reported,” they said. Social media images showed a number of fire tenders at the scene.